"Abstract Every Member State of the European Community has automated information services in one form or another. The quality of those services receives a great deal of attention on the part of the information service providers as well as of the users. The issue of liability for the provision and exploitation of automated information services was the focus of attention of the Legal Advisory Board (LAB) during its May 1989 meeting. The LAB had its disposal twelve country reports which gave a survey of the practical and legal situation with regard to liability in each Member State. Below the main characteristics of the situation within the Community will be described, as well as the main comments made during the LAB meeting"
